For shortcut resoltuion:
	1: check 1st char:
		if ~ or $HOME, abs_pathname starts at $HOME
		if /, abs_pathname starts at /
		else, abs_pathname starts at pwd
	2: split up rest of pathname into an array of strings seperated by /
	3: recursivley do this step for all values in array
		a: if not .. or .
			add it to abs_pathname
		b: if .
			ignore it and move on to next value
		c: if ..
			remove chars from end of abs_pathname until we reach a /

Needs:
	function to split up string into array of strings based on certain char
	function to check if an input is a path(ie, it has a / in it)
